			SUBSTITUTE(
				IF(ISBLANK(pse__Expense__r.pse__Description__c),
					$Label.pse__BillingEventItemExpenseSummaryDescriptionWithNoExpenseDescription,
					SUBSTITUTE($Label.pse__BillingEventItemExpenseSummaryDescription, '{2}', '(' + pse__Expense__r.pse__Description__c + ')')

Override this by entering a comma-separated list of your preferred values. For example, enter Saved,Approved to include only timecards with those statuses.

fields.label: Alerts - Task dates - Milestone
fields.helpText: If selected, an alert graphic and tooltip message displays when Task dates are out of the Milestone target date range.

fields.label: Alerts - Task dates - PTA dates
fields.helpText: If selected, an alert graphic and tooltip message displays when Task dates are out of the Project Task Assignment dates range.

fields.label: Alerts - Task dates - Project
fields.helpText: If selected, an alert graphic and tooltip displays when Task dates are out of the Project start date and end date ranges.

fields.label: Alerts - Task hours - PTA hours
fields.helpText: If selected, an alert graphic and tooltip message displays when task hours are out the range of Project Task assignment hours.

fields.label: Enable Day Detail
fields.helpText: When true, Project Task Gantt offers a Day Detail zoom level, showing the hours scheduled in an expanded day display. The default is false.

fields.label: Hide Preview and Confirmation on Save
fields.helpText: Determines whether a dialog box is displayed every time you click Save. This allows you to review the proposed changes to project tasks before committing them to the actual records in your organization. The setting is deselected by default.

fields.label: Resource Demand Default
fields.helpText: Specifies the default resource demand type when clicking the Create Resource Demand button in Project Task Gantt.  Values are: "resource requests", "held resource requests", or "assignments". The default value is "resource requests".

fields.label: Show Task Notes
fields.helpText: Show Task Notes in Gantt

fields.label: Single Click Task Selection
fields.helpText: Allows you to change default Project Task Gantt task pane selection behavior from double-click to single-click. The setting is deselected by default.

fields.label: Suppress Auto Link Assignment
fields.helpText: When selected, allows you to change the default behavior of Project Task Gantt so that new project task assignments are not linked to existing assignment or resource request. This setting is deselected by default.

fields.label: Zoom Level
fields.helpText: Specifies the default zoom level for the timeline. Valid values are: quarter, month, week, day or daydetail. This setting is set to week by default.

fields.label: Always Allow Breaking Locks
fields.helpText: When a project is locked for editing, this setting determines whether users (who have permission to edit tasks on the Project Task Gantt) are given the option to break the lock and force the other user into read-only mode.

fields.label: Columns Field Set
fields.helpText: Defines the APIname of the field set, on the project task object, that contains the custom columns to show on Project Task Gantt. When the setting is blank, the Gantt Editable Custom Columns field set is used.

fields.label: Disable Buffered Rendering
fields.helpText: If selected, records in Project Task Gantt are not loaded in a buffer.  The default is deselected. This setting should only be changed after consulting Certinia Customer Support.

fields.label: Disable Resolve Dependency Btn on Sync
fields.helpText: If selected the resolve dependency button is deactivated when the project task dependencies are synchronized. If deselected, the button remains active when project task dependencies do not need to be synchronized. The default value is deselected.

fields.label: Leading Buffer Zone
fields.helpText: Determines the number of rows to render above the current view in Project Task Gantt. The default is 20. This setting should only be changed after consulting Certinia Customer Support.

fields.label: Milestone Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: API name of a field set used to display a custom tooltip for Milestones. If defined, this setting replaces the default Milestone tooltip.

fields.label: PTA Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: API name of a field set used to display a custom tooltip for Project Task Assignments. If defined, this setting replaces the default Project Task Assignment tooltip.

fields.label: Project Manager Access
fields.helpText: Determines levels of Gantt edit access for the Project Manager. Values are "Full" (default) - can edit created projects, "Read"- has only read-only access, or "None" - access determined by Permission Controls.

fields.label: Project Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: API name of a field set used to display a custom tooltip for Projects. If defined, this setting replaces the default Project tooltip.

fields.label: Read Only Field Set
fields.helpText: The API name of a field set on a project task containing fields that are not editable in Project Task Gantt.

fields.label: Save Column Preferences
fields.helpText: If selected, customizations to width, order, and visibility of columns in the Project Task Gantt will be remembered per user.

fields.label: Show "Create Resource Demand" button
fields.helpText: If selected, the Create Resource Demand button is shown on the Project Task Gantt toolbar. Use to staff the project plan through the Create Resource Demand button from Project Task Assignments page.

fields.label: Show Hours Completion % in Task Bar
fields.helpText: Determines if the hours complete percentage shows in the task bar display in the Schedule pane. This setting does not control the display of the %Hrs button in the Schedule pane.

fields.label: Show Points Completion % in Task Bar
fields.helpText: Determines if the points complete percentage shows in the task bar display in the Schedule pane. This setting is selected by default. This setting does not control the display of the %Pts button in the Schedule pane.

fields.label: Task Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: API name of a field set used to display a custom tooltip for Project Tasks. If defined, this setting replaces the default Project Task tooltip.

fields.label: Trailing Buffer Zone
fields.helpText: Determines the number of rows to render below the current view in Project Task Gantt. The default is 10. This setting should only be changed after consulting Certinia Customer Support.

fields.label: Display Decimal Precision Cutoff
fields.helpText: The maximum number of hours for which to display decimal places. For example, if set to 100, decimal precision displays for 100 hours or less. The default value is "100"

fields.label: Hide Inline Edit Dialog
fields.helpText: This setting determines whether or not to hide the edit mode settings dialog.

fields.label: Hold total assignment hours constant
fields.helpText: This setting determines how inline editing of assignments affects total assignment hours and end date.

fields.label: Show Project Start/End Date Indicators
fields.helpText: This setting determines if project start and end date indicators display in a project summary bar.  The default value is deselected.

fields.label: Show Shift Management Assignments
fields.helpText: If selected, Shift Management assignments display in Planners.

fields.label: Zoom Level
fields.helpText: The default timeline zoom level. Enter a value of quarter, month, week or day. The default value is "week".

fields.label: Add Holidays On Assignment Adjust
fields.helpText: If selected, determines whether holiday schedule exception records are added if assignment date ranges are adjusted and the new date range falls within a holiday.

fields.label: Allow Mass Move Assignments
fields.helpText: If selected, this setting allows users to drag the assignment bar to mass move assignments in the Project Planner. This setting is deselected by default.

fields.label: Assn Additional Fields Field Set Name
fields.helpText: Determines the additional fields to display in the "Additional Fields" section of the Create Assignment dialog in Project Planner.

fields.label: Assignment Color Field
fields.helpText: Defines the API name of the field on an Assignment that controls the assignment color bars in Project Planner.

fields.label: Assignment Ordering
fields.helpText: This setting defines the API name of a field to order assignments by and, optionally, the direction (ASC or DESC). Assignments always appear above held resource requests.

fields.label: Assignment Search Fieldset Name
fields.helpText: Determines which Assignment fields are searched with the text search box on the project planner.

fields.label: Assignment Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: The API name of the field set that contains the fields to show as tooltips for assignments on the project planner. The field set must exist in the Assignment object.

fields.label: Columns Field Set
fields.helpText: The API name of the field set that contains the columns to show on the project planner. The field set must exist in the Project object.

fields.label: Default Future Days to Show Assignments
fields.helpText: This setting defines the number of future days, from today, for which the enhanced Project Planner will display assignments. For example, enter 30 to display assignments that start or end within 30 days of today.

fields.label: Default Past Days to Show Assignments
fields.helpText: This setting defines the number of days prior to today for which the enhanced Project Planner will display assignments. For example, enter 30 to display assignments that start or end in the preceding 30 days.

fields.label: Default Resource Image
fields.helpText: Defines a URL (absolute or relative) that points to the default image to use for resources without a profile photo. Image files of 22 pixels square work best.

fields.label: Project Planner Filter Field Set
fields.helpText: Determines the fields used for filtering in the Project Planner. The value is a field set specifying fields available to filter on.

fields.label: Hide Cost Rate fields
fields.helpText: When selected, the Cost Rate fields on the Create Assignment dialog will be hidden for all users.

fields.label: DEPRECATED: Hide Inline Edit Dialog
fields.helpText: DEPRECATED: Use Project_Planner_Preferences__c.Hide_Inline_Dialog__c instead.

fields.label: Inherit Dates For Create Assignment
fields.helpText: If selected, the start and end dates in the Create Assignments dialog are auto-populated from the project start and end dates.

fields.label: Inherit Role For Create Assignment
fields.helpText: If selected, the resource role in the Create Assignments dialog is auto-populated from the Contacts record.

fields.helpText: DEPRECATED: Use Project_Planner_Preferences__c.Inline_Edit_Mode_THHC__c instead.

fields.label: Override Assignment Name Field
fields.helpText: Specifies the API name of the assignment to display in Project planner. If this field is blank, the Project planner displays the Assignment name by default.

fields.label: Override Resource Request Name Field
fields.helpText: Specifies the API name of the resource request to display in Project planner. If this field is blank, the Project planner displays the Resource Request name by default.

fields.label: Project Search Fieldset Name
fields.helpText: Determines which Project fields are searched with the text search box on the project planner.

fields.label: Project Summary Color Field
fields.helpText: Defines the API name of the field on a Project that controls the Project Summary colors.

fields.label: Project Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: The API name of the field set that contains the fields to show as tooltips for projects on the project planner. The field set must exist in the Project object.

fields.label: Record Load Limit
fields.helpText: Specifies the number of projects for which child data (assignments and resource requests) load per request. You should not adjust the Record Load Limit without first consulting Customer Support.

fields.label: Resource Request Tooltip Field Set
fields.helpText: The API name of the field set that contains the fields to show as tooltips for resource requests on the project planner. The field set must exist in the Resource Request object.

fields.label: Resource Request Search Fieldset Name
fields.helpText: Determines which Resource Request fields are searched with the text search box on the project planner.

fields.label: Resource Request Color Field
fields.helpText: Defines the API name of the field on a Resource Request that controls the Resource Request color bars in Project Planner.

fields.label: Resource Request Ordering
fields.helpText: This setting defines the API name of a field to order held resource requests by and, optionally, the direction (ASC or DESC). Held resource requests always appear below assignments.

fields.label: Restrict Creation Past Dates
fields.helpText: If selected, you cannot create an assignment with start date in the past. The default value is deselected.

fields.label: Restrict Editing Past Dates
fields.helpText: If selected, you cannot edit Project Planner assignment and schedule hours in the past. The default value is deselected.

fields.label: Restrict Swapping Past Dates
fields.helpText: If selected, you cannot swap the resource on an assignment with a start date set in the past. The default value is deselected.

fields.label: Save Column Preferences
fields.helpText: If selected, customizations to width, order, and visibility of columns in the Project Planner will be remembered per user.

fields.label: Respect Schedules
fields.helpText: When True, schedules and schedule exceptions are respected when assignments or resource requests are dragged and dropped in the Project Planner timeline. Non-working time is respected. The default value is False.

fields.label: Hours
fields.formula:
IF( AND(NOT(ISBLANK(pse__Assignment__c)), NOT(ISBLANK(pse__Assignment__r.pse__Scheduled_Hours__c)) ),
pse__Assignment__r.pse__Scheduled_Hours__c, 
 IF( NOT(ISBLANK(pse__Resource_Request__c)), IF( AND( NOT(ISBLANK(pse__Resource_Request__r.pse__Preferred_Schedule__c)), NOT(ISBLANK( pse__Resource_Request__r.pse__Preferred_Schedule__r.pse__Scheduled_Hours__c)) ), 
pse__Resource_Request__r.pse__Preferred_Schedule__r.pse__Scheduled_Hours__c, 
 IF( NOT(ISBLANK(pse__Resource_Request__r.pse__SOW_Hours__c)), pse__Resource_Request__r.pse__SOW_Hours__c, 0) ), 0) )
fields.helpText: The number of scheduled hours from a related Assignment (if one exists) or, if a Related Resource exists, either the number of hours associated with the Related Resource's Preferred Schedule or the requested number of hours.

fields.label: Hours Remaining
fields.formula:
IF (
			ISBLANK(pse__Estimated_Time_To_Completion__c),
			IF (pse__Estimated_Hours__c - pse__Actual_Hours__c < 0,
				 0, /* Never allow this field to go below 0 */
				 pse__Estimated_Hours__c - pse__Actual_Hours__c
			),
			pse__Estimated_Time_To_Completion__c
		)
fields.helpText: The number of hours remaining to complete the task derived from Estimated Time to Completion (Task) when set. Calculated otherwise from estimated hours minus actual hours.

fields.label: Percent Complete (Hours)
fields.formula:
IF
			( ISBLANK(pse__Estimated_Time_To_Completion__c),
				IF
				( pse__Estimated_Hours__c == 0,
					0, /* 0% on no estimate to match behavior of points */
					pse__Actual_Hours__c/pse__Estimated_Hours__c )
				,
				IF
				( (pse__Estimated_Time_To_Completion__c + pse__Actual_Hours__c == 0),
					0, /* 0% on no estimate to match behavior of points */
					(pse__Actual_Hours__c/(pse__Estimated_Time_To_Completion__c + pse__Actual_Hours__c)) ))

fields.helpText: API name of the custom field on the Expense object that is used to determine the monthly time period any Deliverable expense revenue is added to. This enables you to control the month in which the revenue is placed.

fields.helpText: API name of the custom field on the Milestone object that is used to determine the monthly time period any Deliverable milestone revenue is added to. This enables you to control the month in which milestone revenue is placed.

fields.label: Custom Date for Deliverable Misc Adjusts

fields.helpText: If selected, weighting is applied to % Complete revenue forecast calculations for scheduled and actual hours on assignments and resource requests. fields.label: Total Days Worked
fields.formula:
IF( NOT(ISNULL(pse__Days_Worked_Override__c)),
pse__Days_Worked_Override__c,
IF( NOT(ISNULL(pse__Total_Days_Worked_Advanced__c)),
pse__Total_Days_Worked_Advanced__c,
IF((pse__Sunday_Hours__c>0),1,0) + IF((pse__Monday_Hours__c>0),1,0) + IF((pse__Tuesday_Hours__c>0),1,0) + IF((pse__Wednesday_Hours__c>0),1,0) + IF((pse__Thursday_Hours__c>0),1,0) + IF((pse__Friday_Hours__c>0),1,0) + IF((pse__Saturday_Hours__c>0),1,0)
)
)

fields.label: Total Hours
fields.formula: pse__Sunday_Hours__c + pse__Monday_Hours__c + pse__Tuesday_Hours__c + pse__Wednesday_Hours__c + pse__Thursday_Hours__c + pse__Friday_Hours__c + pse__Saturday_Hours__c

fields.label: PSR Total Billable Hours
fields.formula: IF( pse__Billable__c ,1, 0) * ( pse__Saturday_Hours__c + pse__Sunday_Hours__c + pse__Monday_Hours__c + pse__Tuesday_Hours__c + pse__Wednesday_Hours__c + pse__Thursday_Hours__c + pse__Friday_Hours__c )

fields.label: Remaining Capacity
fields.formula:
IF(pse__Calendar_Hours__c=0,
0,
(pse__Calendar_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Billable_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Excluded_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Credited_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Non_Billable_Hours__c - pse__Held_Hours__c -  pse__Unheld_Hours__c) / pse__Calendar_Hours__c
)

fields.label: Total Hours Opp Pct Weighted
fields.formula: pse__Assigned_Billable_Hours__c + pse__Assigned_Excluded_Hours__c + pse__Assigned_Credited_Hours__c + pse__Assigned_Non_Billable_Hours__c + pse__Held_Hours_Opp_Pct_Weighted__c + pse__Unheld_Hours_Opp_Pct_Weighted__c

fields.label: Total Hours
fields.formula: pse__Assigned_Billable_Hours__c + pse__Assigned_Excluded_Hours__c + pse__Assigned_Credited_Hours__c + pse__Assigned_Non_Billable_Hours__c +  pse__Held_Hours__c + pse__Unheld_Hours__c

fields.label: Remaining Capacity Hours
fields.formula:
IF(pse__Calendar_Hours__c=0,
0,
(pse__Calendar_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Billable_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Excluded_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Credited_Hours__c - pse__Assigned_Non_Billable_Hours__c - pse__Held_Hours__c - pse__Unheld_Hours__c))
